tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul,
  transitioning from a generic look to a calming, sleep-themed design with
  consistent styling across all components and sections. A console error related
  to null input values was also fixed.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic improvement for their
  sleep questionnaire app, aiming for a more professional and calming user
  experience. The agent began by analyzing the existing design, identifying
  areas like the generic color palette, plain backgrounds, and basic form
  elements. The approach involved implementing a new sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigning the main form layout with subtle visual enhancements, and
  polishing individual UI components like checkboxes, sliders, and progress
  bars. The introduction and report sections were also significantly updated for
  better visual hierarchy and thematic consistency. During the process, a
  console error related to null input values in form fields was identified and
  fixed by modifying the  component. Further refinements addressed user
  feedback on inconsistent colors in the report section and involved creating
  global alert utility classes and adjusting section border opacities for a more
  cohesive look. The outcome is an app with a unified, calming aesthetic that
  aligns with its purpose.
